1
00:00:20,395 --> 00:00:21,438
Saebyeok.

2
00:00:22,772 --> 00:00:26,109
Haneul found out today is
your father's memorial day.

3
00:00:27,110 --> 00:00:27,694
It's okay.

4
00:00:28,903 --> 00:00:30,155
I'll talk to him well.

5
00:01:35,095 --> 00:01:41,600
=Never Forget Your Enemy=

6
00:01:42,852 --> 00:01:48,352
=Episode 6=
(Because You Exist)

7
00:01:55,712 --> 00:01:56,352
What are you?

8
00:01:59,712 --> 00:02:00,288
Sorry.

9
00:02:18,778 --> 00:02:19,520
Haneul.

10
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:22,368
Why didn't you tell me?

11
00:02:25,178 --> 00:02:26,688
I didn't know how to tell you.

12
00:02:32,435 --> 00:02:34,229
I was the only one clueless,

13
00:02:35,146 --> 00:02:36,856
preparing your birthday.

14
00:02:47,742 --> 00:02:49,828
I don't understand
why you didn't tell me.

15
00:02:51,371 --> 00:02:53,373
After the accident,
your health wasn't good.

16
00:02:53,915 --> 00:02:55,583
I thought it'd be too much

17
00:02:56,251 --> 00:02:57,752
if you knew about my father too.

18
00:03:01,631 --> 00:03:02,757
So,

19
00:03:03,299 --> 00:03:04,342
if I never remembered,

20
00:03:05,570 --> 00:03:07,070
you were just never going to tell me?

21
00:03:09,222 --> 00:03:10,890
I was going to tell you

22
00:03:11,391 --> 00:03:12,434
once you adjusted.

23
00:03:26,906 --> 00:03:28,366
Even so,

24
00:03:28,867 --> 00:03:29,743
there's mom,

25
00:03:30,201 --> 00:03:31,327
my sister,

26
00:03:33,830 --> 00:03:34,873
and me.

27
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,585
I should've thought it through.

28
00:03:40,587 --> 00:03:41,796
I'm sorry.

29
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:48,887
Let's hold the ancestral rites together.

30
00:05:07,340 --> 00:05:08,091
Eat up.

31
00:05:49,257 --> 00:05:50,216
Let's go.

32
00:05:50,592 --> 00:05:51,200
Where?

33
00:05:55,722 --> 00:05:56,806
Anywhere.

34
00:06:03,646 --> 00:06:04,772
I'll drive.

35
00:06:05,184 --> 00:06:06,752
But you don't remember how to drive.

36
00:06:08,651 --> 00:06:10,028
Maybe my body still remembers.

37
00:06:10,987 --> 00:06:12,405
I'll drive. Let's go.

38
00:06:21,372 --> 00:06:22,707
I'm sorry I can't remember.

39
00:06:24,334 --> 00:06:25,501
Don't say that.

40
00:06:28,379 --> 00:06:29,184
It was an accident.

41
00:06:29,714 --> 00:06:30,840
That was four years ago.

42
00:06:33,676 --> 00:06:34,469
I see.

43
00:06:35,872 --> 00:06:36,992
You must've had a hard time.

44
00:06:40,850 --> 00:06:42,560
I was okay because I had you.

45
00:06:44,187 --> 00:06:45,063
That's a relief.

46
00:06:49,984 --> 00:06:51,264
Please stay with me.

47
00:06:54,781 --> 00:06:55,490
Okay.

48
00:06:56,574 --> 00:06:58,034
I'll definitely be by your side.

49
00:07:11,589 --> 00:07:12,465
Yeo Saebyeok.

50
00:07:13,466 --> 00:07:14,008
Hmm?

51
00:07:15,677 --> 00:07:16,886
I remembered

52
00:07:17,595 --> 00:07:18,596
something else.

53
00:07:18,763 --> 00:07:19,514
What is it?

54
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:22,642
Well...

55
00:07:24,185 --> 00:07:25,770
it's what I said to you

56
00:07:26,646 --> 00:07:28,356
after you hurt my leg.

57
00:07:31,651 --> 00:07:33,111
That it was your fault.

58
00:07:36,447 --> 00:07:37,740
It was just an accident.

59
00:07:40,827 --> 00:07:42,245
I'm sorry I blamed you.

60
00:07:43,997 --> 00:07:44,872
Haneul.

61
00:07:45,952 --> 00:07:46,457
Hmm?

62
00:07:47,709 --> 00:07:49,168
I wish everything about you

63
00:07:49,585 --> 00:07:51,212
could be my fault.

64
00:07:52,964 --> 00:07:55,008
So you'd never blame yourself.

65
00:07:58,511 --> 00:07:59,512
I'd rather you blame me

66
00:08:00,388 --> 00:08:02,724
than carry guilt in your life.

67
00:08:06,464 --> 00:08:07,564
What are you talking about?

68
00:08:09,814 --> 00:08:10,565
You think

69
00:08:11,190 --> 00:08:13,067
I'd let you carry everything alone?

70
00:08:15,528 --> 00:08:16,446
I just

71
00:08:17,780 --> 00:08:19,365
want you to be happy, Haneul.

72
00:08:23,703 --> 00:08:24,829
Let's do it together.

73
00:08:28,875 --> 00:08:30,043
Let's be happy

74
00:08:30,209 --> 00:08:31,127
together.

75
00:09:09,957 --> 00:09:10,833
Yeo Saebyeok.

76
00:09:11,084 --> 00:09:11,709
Are you okay?

77
00:09:13,586 --> 00:09:14,504
Hmm...

78
00:09:40,738 --> 00:09:41,489
Don't get sick.

79
00:09:45,618 --> 00:09:46,744
Happy birthday.

80
00:09:48,412 --> 00:09:49,372
Saebyeok.

81
00:10:23,152 --> 00:10:25,152
I should've blown out
the birthday candles for you.

82
00:10:44,552 --> 00:10:46,929
There doesn't seem to be
any major issue.

83
00:10:48,556 --> 00:10:49,265
Lately,

84
00:10:49,891 --> 00:10:51,616
I've been having frequent headaches,

85
00:10:51,767 --> 00:10:53,144
and sometimes I feel dizzy.

86
00:10:54,020 --> 00:10:56,981
Those symptoms can come
with recovering memories.

87
00:10:57,773 --> 00:11:00,902
It can be considered a psychogenic
headache, not neurological.

88
00:11:02,653 --> 00:11:05,072
Is there any way
to recover my memories faster?

89
00:11:06,782 --> 00:11:11,537
It's a defense mechanism where your brain
blocks memories to protect itself.

90
00:11:12,205 --> 00:11:16,542
So forcing them back too quickly
can cause more confusion and anxiety.

91
00:11:18,377 --> 00:11:21,339
Since I can't remember things
that were very important to me,

92
00:11:22,882 --> 00:11:25,468
it feels like a huge
part of my life is missing.

93
00:11:26,302 --> 00:11:27,929
So sometimes I feel empty,

94
00:11:29,555 --> 00:11:31,098
like I'm missing something important

95
00:11:31,766 --> 00:11:32,391
and anxious.

96
00:11:33,351 --> 00:11:35,269
That sense of emptiness

97
00:11:35,353 --> 00:11:38,314
is common in patients
with dissociative amnesia.

98
00:11:39,482 --> 00:11:41,400
It's the brain's way
of protecting itself.

99
00:11:41,484 --> 00:11:44,445
A natural response that occurs
when memories are blocked.

100
00:11:44,695 --> 00:11:47,156
You're not doing anything wrong.

101
00:11:54,497 --> 00:11:55,623
That's all for today.

102
00:11:56,499 --> 00:11:57,875
- Great job, everyone!
- Yes!

103
00:12:02,336 --> 00:12:04,032
(It would help if you could write down)

104
00:12:04,340 --> 00:12:06,342
(and organize anything
that comes back to you.)

105
00:12:16,218 --> 00:12:17,888
(Coach's Feedback)

106
00:12:17,888 --> 00:12:20,540
(Shouted at the coach;
Threw the ring; Why? Who took it?)

107
00:12:20,540 --> 00:12:23,200
(So wasteful; Where did it go?)

108
00:12:29,573 --> 00:12:31,784
I can't seem to find any connection.

109
00:12:49,248 --> 00:12:51,226
(Top star Yeo Saebyeok's dating rumors
revealed to be a hoax by anti-fans)

110
00:12:55,816 --> 00:12:56,516
(Top Star Yeo Saebyeok and Sohyun)

111
00:12:56,516 --> 00:12:57,216
(Dating Rumors Denied)
Thank goodness.

112
00:12:57,216 --> 00:12:58,304
("Photos were manipulated
and spread by anti-fans")

113
00:12:59,228 --> 00:13:00,688
Hyung! Where are you now?

114
00:13:06,736 --> 00:13:07,778
Ta-da.

115
00:13:08,029 --> 00:13:08,821
What?

116
00:13:09,405 --> 00:13:10,573
Are you feeling better?

117
00:13:11,449 --> 00:13:12,416
What brings you here?

118
00:13:12,700 --> 00:13:13,909
To see the celebrities.

119
00:13:21,542 --> 00:13:22,168
What is he?

120
00:13:22,460 --> 00:13:23,711
Ah, he went to take a call.

121
00:13:24,086 --> 00:13:25,568
But seriously, what brings you here?

122
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:27,423
Did you see the article?

123
00:13:28,758 --> 00:13:29,884
He showed me earlier.

124
00:13:31,552 --> 00:13:33,512
My ability is this strong.

125
00:13:34,055 --> 00:13:34,680
How is it?

126
00:13:35,681 --> 00:13:36,768
It's really reassuring.

127
00:13:40,061 --> 00:13:41,632
I'm really glad it was resolved well.

128
00:13:41,824 --> 00:13:42,912
It's all thanks to you.

129
00:13:43,264 --> 00:13:43,840
Thank you.

130
00:13:46,984 --> 00:13:48,152
By the way...

131
00:13:53,449 --> 00:13:55,076
You were the most handsome.

132
00:14:11,300 --> 00:14:12,176
What?

133
00:14:14,053 --> 00:14:15,221
You're the patient.

134
00:14:17,390 --> 00:14:18,724
Trying to pass it on to you.

135
00:14:24,355 --> 00:14:26,315
(Okay, shoot's going in. Ready.)

136
00:14:28,275 --> 00:14:28,776
Action.

137
00:14:49,713 --> 00:14:51,215
Does he have to stay here

138
00:14:51,632 --> 00:14:52,925
until it's all filmed?

139
00:14:53,217 --> 00:14:54,343
Looks like it.

140
00:14:55,719 --> 00:14:56,720
When will it end?

141
00:14:57,805 --> 00:15:00,015
Probably around midnight today.

142
00:15:02,435 --> 00:15:03,227
That'll be tough.

143
00:15:10,359 --> 00:15:11,068
Hyung.

144
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:15,197
What does Saebyeok like about me?

145
00:15:16,282 --> 00:15:17,074
Huh?

146
00:15:17,408 --> 00:15:19,712
Weren't things really cold
between you two until recently?

147
00:15:20,995 --> 00:15:22,663
- Not at all.
- Wow.

148
00:15:23,038 --> 00:15:24,832
I feel like I can see

149
00:15:25,040 --> 00:15:26,584
why you two click so well.

150
00:15:30,546 --> 00:15:31,714
Yeo Saebyeok

151
00:15:32,131 --> 00:15:33,568
got it right from the start, right?

152
00:15:33,716 --> 00:15:35,176
Oh, come on.

153
00:15:35,384 --> 00:15:37,219
Saebyeok also went through a lot.

154
00:15:38,345 --> 00:15:39,054
Seriously...

155
00:15:39,346 --> 00:15:40,222
with that face?

156
00:15:40,514 --> 00:15:41,348
Of course.

157
00:15:42,016 --> 00:15:43,893
Getting hurt, getting cut...

158
00:15:44,101 --> 00:15:45,853
Getting cursed at, getting kicked out...

159
00:15:46,624 --> 00:15:48,704
Don't even mention it.
All sorts of things happened.

160
00:15:50,065 --> 00:15:52,693
Yeo Saebyeok didn't
just get that easily.

161
00:15:56,989 --> 00:15:58,073
I really didn't know.

162
00:16:00,326 --> 00:16:02,119
I haven't known Saebyeok for long,

163
00:16:02,745 --> 00:16:04,705
but I can say one thing for sure.

164
00:16:05,956 --> 00:16:09,293
Yeo Saebyeok hasn't gotten
anything easily in life.

165
00:16:10,002 --> 00:16:10,794
Work,

166
00:16:12,192 --> 00:16:13,255
and Gi Haneul, you too.

167
00:16:14,340 --> 00:16:15,382
Oh, what?

168
00:16:15,872 --> 00:16:18,093
Are you hyping him up just
because you're his manager?

169
00:16:18,093 --> 00:16:19,328
What are you talking about?

170
00:16:19,678 --> 00:16:21,597
I may look like this,
but I'm still objective.

171
00:16:22,681 --> 00:16:23,474
Anyone can see that

172
00:16:24,640 --> 00:16:25,824
arm's bent inward, huh?

173
00:16:26,644 --> 00:16:28,437
Arms curve inward.

174
00:16:28,687 --> 00:16:30,523
Forced the other way, they snap.

175
00:16:35,354 --> 00:16:37,526
Okay, we're rolling. Ready.

176
00:16:48,874 --> 00:16:49,708
Apologize.

177
00:16:51,919 --> 00:16:53,952
It's not really something
to apologize for, is it?

178
00:16:54,213 --> 00:16:57,716
What if I'd been carrying a birthday cake,
completely in the dark?

179
00:16:58,342 --> 00:17:00,094
It was his birthday anyway.

180
00:17:00,594 --> 00:17:02,638
It's not like Saebyeok wouldn't get it.

181
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:05,891
It's just because I feel sorry.

182
00:17:06,141 --> 00:17:06,642
Oh, wow.

183
00:17:07,017 --> 00:17:09,632
You've finally matured.
You get what it means to be sorry, huh?

184
00:17:10,396 --> 00:17:11,136
Yes.

185
00:17:13,232 --> 00:17:14,858
Do you remember anything?

186
00:17:16,068 --> 00:17:17,861
Just... bits and pieces?

187
00:17:19,029 --> 00:17:21,991
But I can't remember
the important things.

188
00:17:22,624 --> 00:17:23,744
What about the hospital?

189
00:17:23,909 --> 00:17:24,994
Are you going regularly?

190
00:17:25,536 --> 00:17:26,537
I went yesterday.

191
00:17:26,704 --> 00:17:28,080
What did the doctor say?

192
00:17:29,498 --> 00:17:31,834
The doctor said it's not my fault.

193
00:17:32,918 --> 00:17:34,128
Then why do I...

194
00:17:34,670 --> 00:17:36,422
always feel like I'm at fault?

195
00:17:39,466 --> 00:17:41,635
It's terrifying that
Saebyeok is handling

196
00:17:43,971 --> 00:17:44,888
everything alone.

197
00:17:45,556 --> 00:17:46,348
Gi Haneul.

198
00:17:47,891 --> 00:17:50,144
Just as much as Saebyeok is handling,

199
00:17:50,603 --> 00:17:52,771
you're also handling your part.

200
00:17:54,148 --> 00:17:55,232
Maybe

201
00:17:55,774 --> 00:17:58,319
you're filling in your own new answers

202
00:17:58,819 --> 00:18:02,823
on a blank test sheet,
without knowing the set answers.

203
00:18:04,325 --> 00:18:07,036
Whether they're right
or wrong doesn't really matter.

204
00:18:08,245 --> 00:18:09,038
I just

205
00:18:10,414 --> 00:18:11,582
hope you...

206
00:18:12,499 --> 00:18:14,710
live happily, that's all.

207
00:18:15,127 --> 00:18:15,794
A guest is here.

208
00:18:16,837 --> 00:18:18,714
That was such a cool
older-sister moment...

209
00:18:19,632 --> 00:18:20,633
Junghan, you came.

210
00:18:21,258 --> 00:18:22,760
Haneul, when did you get here?

211
00:18:23,636 --> 00:18:25,596
Ah, if I'd known, I'd have come earlier.

212
00:18:26,096 --> 00:18:28,432
When I asked if you could
come earlier, you said no.

213
00:18:28,807 --> 00:18:29,391
Me?

214
00:18:30,208 --> 00:18:31,648
I couldn't possibly have said that.

215
00:18:32,603 --> 00:18:33,440
What a funny guy.

216
00:18:34,438 --> 00:18:37,107
Since I called you to cover today,
I'll just let it slide.

217
00:18:37,696 --> 00:18:39,040
Take care of closing today, okay?

218
00:18:39,985 --> 00:18:40,800
I'll help you.

219
00:18:41,070 --> 00:18:41,824
Really?

220
00:18:42,488 --> 00:18:43,776
Are you worried about me?

221
00:18:43,776 --> 00:18:44,800
What's gotten into you?

222
00:18:44,998 --> 00:18:46,850
Saebyeok also went for
a shoot out of town

223
00:18:46,850 --> 00:18:48,410
and will only be back the next morning.

224
00:18:48,410 --> 00:18:50,016
Anyway, it's such a relief

225
00:18:50,245 --> 00:18:52,247
that Saebyeok's matter is settled.

226
00:18:52,247 --> 00:18:53,999
It was nonsense from the start.

227
00:18:54,208 --> 00:18:55,968
The only person
who really knows Yeo Saebyeok

228
00:18:56,096 --> 00:18:57,152
is me.

229
00:19:03,050 --> 00:19:03,842
(What are you?)

230
00:19:09,306 --> 00:19:10,474
You punk.

231
00:19:11,725 --> 00:19:12,768
What are you up to?

232
00:19:13,952 --> 00:19:15,328
Wrap up the Yeo Saebyeok's scandal

233
00:19:15,729 --> 00:19:16,832
quietly.

234
00:19:16,832 --> 00:19:18,774
Who are you to boss me around?

235
00:19:19,066 --> 00:19:22,027
Gi Haneul is nice, so he probably
just told you to watch your mouth.

236
00:19:22,820 --> 00:19:24,544
But I'm not exactly
the nice type, you know?

237
00:19:24,963 --> 00:19:26,323
Did Saebyeok order you to do this?

238
00:19:26,323 --> 00:19:28,512
Since he didn't ask,
I took the initiative.

239
00:19:28,659 --> 00:19:30,035
This lunatic...

240
00:19:30,285 --> 00:19:32,162
If only Yeo Saebyeok had been excluded,

241
00:19:33,152 --> 00:19:34,560
I wouldn't have had to do this.

242
00:19:35,136 --> 00:19:35,648
Hey.

243
00:19:35,904 --> 00:19:37,167
Don't you know reporting this

244
00:19:37,459 --> 00:19:40,003
could be seen as threats
or false accusation?

245
00:19:40,963 --> 00:19:42,840
I haven't threatened you yet,

246
00:19:43,584 --> 00:19:45,920
and I have too much evidence
for it to be false accusation.

247
00:19:46,677 --> 00:19:47,720
You punk...

248
00:19:50,889 --> 00:19:51,890
What do you want?

249
00:19:54,351 --> 00:19:56,270
Issue a corrected report on the scandal,

250
00:19:56,270 --> 00:19:58,230
and announce that all the photos
were manipulated.

251
00:19:59,106 --> 00:20:02,735
Whether you confess or blame
someone else, it's not my concern.

252
00:20:03,652 --> 00:20:04,570
Handle it yourself.

253
00:20:05,654 --> 00:20:06,321
Got it?

254
00:20:06,572 --> 00:20:07,072
You!

255
00:20:08,031 --> 00:20:09,760
What's your relationship
with Yeo Saebyeok?

256
00:20:12,578 --> 00:20:13,620
A love triangle?

257
00:20:14,288 --> 00:20:15,873
You punk!

258
00:20:16,915 --> 00:20:20,210
Don't think too much
and get bitten by a crazy dog,

259
00:20:21,503 --> 00:20:22,963
just do well and live long.

260
00:20:27,634 --> 00:20:30,053
And be sincere with your family
from now on.

261
00:20:32,723 --> 00:20:33,348
Hey, you punk!

262
00:20:33,891 --> 00:20:35,893
Why bring up family here? Darn it!

263
00:20:38,020 --> 00:20:39,563
Thanks for helping me today.

264
00:20:39,897 --> 00:20:42,316
Don't go reporting her
as a bad boss somewhere.

265
00:20:42,691 --> 00:20:44,526
Let's go. I'll take you home.

266
00:20:45,402 --> 00:20:46,560
You don't know where I live.

267
00:20:46,653 --> 00:20:47,321
I know.

268
00:20:47,654 --> 00:20:48,864
I went there once before.

269
00:20:49,531 --> 00:20:50,741
You came to my house?

270
00:20:51,492 --> 00:20:53,869
I went to drop off
something you left at the cafe,

271
00:20:54,453 --> 00:20:55,424
but you weren't there.

272
00:20:56,538 --> 00:20:58,499
I only saw Saebyeok briefly at the door.

273
00:20:59,424 --> 00:21:00,000
Yeah?

274
00:21:00,751 --> 00:21:02,368
Saebyeok didn't say anything like that.

275
00:21:02,836 --> 00:21:05,297
I'm going to meet a friend anyway.

276
00:21:05,839 --> 00:21:07,648
Then, let's go together
just to the bus stop.

277
00:21:07,744 --> 00:21:08,288
Okay.

278
00:21:09,696 --> 00:21:10,219
Haneul.

279
00:21:10,592 --> 00:21:11,168
Hmm?

280
00:21:13,096 --> 00:21:13,972
I like you.

281
00:21:15,641 --> 00:21:16,225
Me too.

282
00:21:17,476 --> 00:21:18,185
Really?

283
00:21:18,602 --> 00:21:19,478
Of course.

284
00:21:20,437 --> 00:21:24,608
Who would dislike someone
as handsome, tall, and sincere as you?

285
00:21:25,275 --> 00:21:26,902
Even passersby would like you.

286
00:21:27,903 --> 00:21:28,904
You know,

287
00:21:29,196 --> 00:21:31,198
our regular, little Eunji.

288
00:21:31,490 --> 00:21:33,784
She's always looking for handsome guys.

289
00:21:35,285 --> 00:21:36,829
But I genuinely like you.

290
00:21:43,585 --> 00:21:44,586
Thanks.

291
00:21:44,960 --> 00:21:46,505
You look like you don't believe me.

292
00:21:48,090 --> 00:21:48,966
Well,

293
00:21:49,758 --> 00:21:51,301
we don't really suit each other.

294
00:21:54,847 --> 00:21:55,681
Junghan.

295
00:21:56,098 --> 00:21:57,182
I'll go first.

296
00:22:03,939 --> 00:22:04,940
Cheers.

297
00:22:16,660 --> 00:22:18,537
How's the tennis going
since you started again?

298
00:22:18,912 --> 00:22:19,580
Good.

299
00:22:20,416 --> 00:22:21,920
I shouldn't have quit back then.

300
00:22:23,458 --> 00:22:26,144
It's good enough that
you get to do what you want now.

301
00:22:27,421 --> 00:22:28,046
You are right.

302
00:22:28,505 --> 00:22:29,214
I'm jealous.

303
00:22:30,716 --> 00:22:33,302
Does that handsome guy
at your sister's cafe still work there?

304
00:22:34,219 --> 00:22:34,928
Who?

305
00:22:36,555 --> 00:22:37,347
Junghan?

306
00:22:38,140 --> 00:22:39,099
Yeah, he's fine.

307
00:22:40,851 --> 00:22:42,185
Why that reaction?

308
00:22:42,644 --> 00:22:44,229
Weren't you two getting along?

309
00:22:44,938 --> 00:22:47,441
It seems like you're uncomfortable
talking about him.

310
00:22:53,488 --> 00:22:55,490
I've got a feeling.

311
00:22:56,064 --> 00:22:56,783
What do you mean?

312
00:22:56,783 --> 00:22:57,760
He likes you, right?

313
00:22:57,760 --> 00:22:58,432
What?

314
00:22:58,619 --> 00:22:59,202
No.

315
00:22:59,870 --> 00:23:01,246
Yes, he does.

316
00:23:02,039 --> 00:23:03,373
I knew this would happen.

317
00:23:03,749 --> 00:23:06,710
The way he looked at you wasn't normal.

318
00:23:09,338 --> 00:23:10,339
Gi Haneul.

319
00:23:11,089 --> 00:23:13,216
It feels like just yesterday
you confessed to me.

320
00:23:13,467 --> 00:23:15,136
For me, it really feels like yesterday.

321
00:23:16,386 --> 00:23:18,430
Ah, right. That makes sense for you.

322
00:23:20,557 --> 00:23:23,852
If it weren't for Yeo Saebyeok back then,
I would have kept dating you.

323
00:23:24,686 --> 00:23:26,772
Yeo Saebyeok, that bad guy!

324
00:23:27,898 --> 00:23:29,107
He's bad to me,

325
00:23:29,566 --> 00:23:30,609
but why bad to you?

326
00:23:32,319 --> 00:23:32,896
What?

327
00:23:33,528 --> 00:23:34,848
You seriously don't know?

328
00:23:36,114 --> 00:23:36,704
What?

329
00:23:38,116 --> 00:23:41,824
Why did Yeo Saebyeok have
to mess with my peaceful heart?

330
00:23:42,329 --> 00:23:46,333
And why did he keep getting tangled up
with other women?

331
00:23:48,126 --> 00:23:49,127
It's all

332
00:23:50,504 --> 00:23:52,255
because of you.

333
00:23:52,512 --> 00:23:53,024
Me?

334
00:23:53,924 --> 00:23:54,528
Yes.

335
00:23:55,759 --> 00:23:58,387
The great actor Yeo Saebyeok

336
00:23:59,012 --> 00:24:01,880
hated seeing me with you, Gi Haneul.

337
00:24:01,880 --> 00:24:03,520
He knowingly accepted
others' confessions,

338
00:24:03,520 --> 00:24:07,396
even confessed to me himself,
and then dumped me after just one week!

339
00:24:08,981 --> 00:24:11,316
Just thinking about that
tears my heart apart.

340
00:24:12,090 --> 00:24:12,673
Is that true?

341
00:24:14,400 --> 00:24:15,808
My heart being torn apart?

342
00:24:16,594 --> 00:24:20,064
Or was it Yeo Saebyeok,
overprotecting you from the start?

343
00:24:20,765 --> 00:24:21,641
I didn't know.

344
00:24:23,434 --> 00:24:24,393
So,

345
00:24:25,520 --> 00:24:26,187
you are

346
00:24:26,771 --> 00:24:27,814
pure evil.

347
00:24:30,233 --> 00:24:32,026
Truly a love of the century, really.

348
00:24:37,274 --> 00:24:43,642
(Dummy)

349
00:24:56,602 --> 00:24:57,728
Where is this?

350
00:24:59,584 --> 00:25:00,736
Should I go there tomorrow?

351
00:25:10,624 --> 00:25:11,552
(What are you doing?)

352
00:25:21,466 --> 00:25:22,391
(Haneul.)

353
00:25:35,104 --> 00:25:36,225
Haneul.

354
00:25:44,442 --> 00:25:45,026
Don't cry.

355
00:25:48,863 --> 00:25:49,363
I'm sorry.

356
00:25:52,241 --> 00:25:53,367
It's all my fault.

357
00:25:54,952 --> 00:25:56,454
No, Haneul.

358
00:25:57,330 --> 00:25:57,872
No.

359
00:25:58,664 --> 00:25:59,707
I'm so scared.

360
00:26:06,797 --> 00:26:09,175
I'm no longer
just a happy memory for you.

361
00:26:10,134 --> 00:26:11,135
Don't say that.

362
00:26:13,596 --> 00:26:14,972
I'll cling to your ankles

363
00:26:16,933 --> 00:26:18,517
like a shadow forever.

364
00:26:20,228 --> 00:26:22,813
I'll end up ruining everything.

365
00:26:23,481 --> 00:26:24,398
It's okay to ruin it.

366
00:26:25,066 --> 00:26:26,192
It's okay to fall apart.

367
00:26:31,822 --> 00:26:33,407
Please, just stay by my side.

368
00:26:37,078 --> 00:26:37,703
Let's live.

369
00:26:38,913 --> 00:26:39,956
Let's live together.

370
00:26:48,128 --> 00:26:49,664
Haneul, where are you?

371
00:26:50,716 --> 00:26:51,467
What should I do?

372
00:26:52,301 --> 00:26:52,864
What's wrong?

373
00:26:53,472 --> 00:26:54,336
Did something happen?

374
00:26:55,744 --> 00:26:56,672
It's nothing.

375
00:26:57,598 --> 00:26:58,266
See you later.

376
00:26:59,392 --> 00:27:00,768
Okay, I'll be there soon.

377
00:27:39,682 --> 00:27:40,558
Hello?

378
00:27:42,268 --> 00:27:43,019
Yes.

379
00:27:43,394 --> 00:27:44,937
This is Gi Haneul.

380
00:27:48,107 --> 00:27:48,983
What?

381
00:27:49,859 --> 00:27:50,943
Lee Seri?

382
00:27:55,698 --> 00:27:56,407
Excuse me.

383
00:27:57,074 --> 00:27:58,492
Please go to Seobu Police Station.

384
00:28:03,956 --> 00:28:04,480
Hyung.

385
00:28:04,707 --> 00:28:06,167
I think I need to go see Haneul now.

386
00:28:06,667 --> 00:28:07,168
Why?

387
00:28:07,251 --> 00:28:08,586
Did something happen to Haneul?

388
00:28:08,961 --> 00:28:10,004
I don't know.

389
00:28:10,463 --> 00:28:11,797
But his voice sounded really bad.

390
00:28:15,744 --> 00:28:17,952
Regarding the hit-and-run case
involving Mr. Gi Haneul.

391
00:28:18,095 --> 00:28:19,722
The perpetrator has turned himself in.

392
00:28:26,848 --> 00:28:27,396
Haneul.

393
00:28:28,856 --> 00:28:29,565
Hello?

394
00:28:40,672 --> 00:28:41,888
(I'm going to turn myself in.)

395
00:28:42,286 --> 00:28:45,623
Are you crazy? How can you say that?

396
00:28:46,040 --> 00:28:48,125
You've got no one but me.

397
00:28:48,167 --> 00:28:52,129
If you go to prison now, no one
will come for you. Do you understand?

398
00:28:53,005 --> 00:28:53,506
There is...

399
00:28:54,528 --> 00:28:55,200
one person.

400
00:28:56,759 --> 00:29:01,536
Han Jeongyun said he'll confess everything
only if you come, so I had to call you.

401
00:29:02,223 --> 00:29:03,307
Yoon Junghan...

402
00:29:04,642 --> 00:29:06,435
I don't know if you heard,

403
00:29:06,936 --> 00:29:09,188
but he admitted this wasn't
Han Jeongyun's solo act.

404
00:29:09,563 --> 00:29:11,732
He confessed that
Lee Seri put him up to it.

405
00:29:12,483 --> 00:29:13,859
You remember Lee Seri, right?

406
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:15,111
No.

407
00:29:16,070 --> 00:29:17,571
By any chance, recently,

408
00:29:18,030 --> 00:29:21,117
have you received
any threatening letters from Lee Seri?

409
00:29:24,203 --> 00:29:24,912
Threatening...

410
00:29:25,496 --> 00:29:26,414
letters?

411
00:29:27,498 --> 00:29:30,543
Lee Seri claimed that
you would know all about it.

412
00:31:18,108 --> 00:31:21,070
(The murderer is you, Gi Haneul)

413
00:31:48,305 --> 00:31:49,431
It's Han Jeongyun.

414
00:31:50,391 --> 00:31:51,308
My name.

415
00:31:53,811 --> 00:31:54,979
Why did you do that?

416
00:31:57,481 --> 00:31:59,233
At first, I wanted to kill.

417
00:32:01,235 --> 00:32:02,695
Then it was curiosity.

418
00:32:05,030 --> 00:32:06,115
In the end,

419
00:32:07,992 --> 00:32:09,159
I wanted to make it right.

420
00:32:12,256 --> 00:32:13,581
Junghan.

421
00:32:14,748 --> 00:32:17,209
In the orphanage,
they randomly give names.

422
00:32:19,503 --> 00:32:22,464
That's why I hated living
as Han Jeongyun.

423
00:32:24,758 --> 00:32:25,759
What did I do wrong?

424
00:32:26,635 --> 00:32:27,720
Wrongdoings

425
00:32:28,596 --> 00:32:30,180
are things bad people do.

426
00:32:32,891 --> 00:32:34,685
But you're a good person.

427
00:32:40,357 --> 00:32:42,776
Everything you know about me is false.

428
00:32:49,199 --> 00:32:50,200
I love you.

429
00:32:53,248 --> 00:32:54,288
This part is for real.

430
00:33:11,218 --> 00:33:14,255
♪The more I try to run away♪

431
00:33:14,553 --> 00:33:16,236
♪The clearer it becomes♪

432
00:33:17,838 --> 00:33:21,128
♪Even the word "love"♪

433
00:33:21,424 --> 00:33:22,615
♪Can't convey how I feel♪

434
00:33:24,684 --> 00:33:27,757
♪Watching your shadow moving forward♪

435
00:33:27,986 --> 00:33:29,618
♪Sometimes, I resent you♪

436
00:33:29,618 --> 00:33:31,456
♪But without you,
everything feels strange♪

437
00:33:31,709 --> 00:33:36,779
♪The pain also makes me grow♪

438
00:33:38,226 --> 00:33:40,126
♪There is a lot to say♪

439
00:33:40,126 --> 00:33:41,546
♪Trying to separate us♪

440
00:33:41,859 --> 00:33:44,704
♪Even if I look like a fool♪

441
00:33:45,300 --> 00:33:46,820
♪It doesn't matter♪

442
00:33:46,820 --> 00:33:48,786
♪This is how we are♪

443
00:33:48,786 --> 00:33:51,701
♪Connected to each other♪

444
00:33:51,762 --> 00:33:55,281
♪We are truly strange♪

445
00:33:55,762 --> 00:33:58,813
♪Pushing each other away,
yet embracing again♪

446
00:33:58,813 --> 00:34:01,106
♪Between love and pain♪

447
00:34:01,138 --> 00:34:04,149
♪In some corner♪

448
00:34:04,300 --> 00:34:07,785
♪In the end, we can only be together♪

449
00:34:14,892 --> 00:34:18,724
♪Because that's us♪

450
00:34:22,178 --> 00:34:23,538
♪Even if what we said yesterday♪

451
00:34:23,538 --> 00:34:24,992
♪Remains in the heart♪

452
00:34:25,170 --> 00:34:26,962
♪As time passes♪

453
00:34:26,962 --> 00:34:28,178
♪Maybe I'll laugh about it♪

454
00:34:28,178 --> 00:34:30,258
♪Even those painful memories♪

455
00:34:30,258 --> 00:34:31,378
♪Are also ours♪

456
00:34:31,532 --> 00:34:34,112
♪Seems we can♪

457
00:34:34,112 --> 00:34:36,049
♪Be more understanding♪

458
00:34:36,524 --> 00:34:38,708
♪I clearly told myself♪

459
00:34:39,730 --> 00:34:41,988
♪Never to see you again♪

460
00:34:42,226 --> 00:34:44,935
♪But hearing your voice♪

461
00:34:45,292 --> 00:34:46,322
♪I completely break down♪

462
00:34:49,132 --> 00:34:52,114
♪Even if hearts that meet♪

463
00:34:52,620 --> 00:34:55,299
♪Bring wounds, they always♪
